'''纳米马达'''是一种能够将[[能量|能量]]转化为[[机械能|机械能]]的[[分子|分子]]或[[纳米|纳米]]级装置<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Dreyfus | first1 = R. | last2 = Baudry | first2 = J. | last3 = Roper | first3 = M. L. | last4 = Fermigier | first4 = M. | last5 = Stone | first5 = H. A. | last6 = Bibette | first6 = J. | year = 2005 | title = Microscopic artificial swimmers | journal = Nature | volume = 437 | issue = 7060| pages = 862–5 | doi=10.1038/nature04090| pmid = 16208366 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Bamrungsap | first1 = S. | last2 = Phillips | first2 = J. A. | last3 = Xiong | first3 = X. | last4 = Kim | first4 = Y. | last5 = Wang | first5 = H. | last6 = Liu | first6 = H. | last7 = Hebard | first7 = A. | last8 = Tan | first8 = W. | year = 2011 | title = Magnetically driven single DNA nanomotor | journal = Small | volume = 7 | issue = 5| pages = 601–605 | doi=10.1002/smll.201001559| pmid = 21370463 }}</ref>。

自然界中就存在纳米马达，例如[[细菌|细菌]]、[[精子|精子]]等具有[[鞭毛|鞭毛]]的[[细胞|细胞]], 通过[[三磷酸腺苷|三磷酸腺苷]]或[[质子|质子]]供能的[[蛋白质|蛋白质]]马达摆动鞭毛，从而实现自主运动<ref>{{cite book |title=The phototrophic prokaryotes |publisher=Springer |location=New York |isbn=978-1-4613-7188-5 |url=https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-1-4615-4827-0}}</ref><ref name="TB-2020-0323">{{cite journal |last1=Wu |first1=Jianrong |last2=Zheng |first2=Yuanyi |last3=Li |first3=Maoyao |title=Principles and biomedical applications of light-poweredmicro/nanomotors |journal=Chinese Science Bulletin |date=2020-12-01 |volume=65 |issue=35 |pages=4123–4138 |doi=10.1360/TB-2020-0323}}</ref>。

人工纳米马达是[[仿生|仿生]]自然界中纳米马达的一种材料，用于[[核酸|核酸]]、[[蛋白质|蛋白质]]和[[药物运输|药物运输]]、[[癌症诊断|癌症诊断]]、[[无创显微手术|无创显微手术]]、[[化学传感|化学传感]]、[[环境修复|环境修复]]等领域<ref name="TB-2020-0323" />。根据能量来源不同，可分为化学驱动、物理场驱动以及混合动力驱动的纳米马达<ref name="TB-2020-0323" />。

